#compdef echoip
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# echoip — minimal IP-address-and-context lookup HTTP service: returns
#          plain text / JSON / HTML with the requester's IP + country
#          flag + city + ASN + reverse DNS + open ports (curl-friendly,
#          the canonical reference deployment is https://ifconfig.co)
#          (Go, 4313★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/mpolden/echoip
#           (the public canonical instance is https://ifconfig.co)
# author : Martin Polden (mpolden) — the author also runs ifconfig.co
#          as the reference deployment of this codebase
# license: BSD-3-Clause
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from
# cmd/echoip/main.go on the mpolden/echoip tip — the stdlib `flag`
# package `flag.String(...)` / `flag.Bool(...)` / `flag.Int(...)` /
# `flag.Var(...)` registrations parsed exactly as declared, preserving
# the single-letter-only convention typical of stdlib `flag` (no
# long-form aliases — flags from `flag` are single-dash by tradition).
#
# Direct deps from go.mod (selected):
#   github.com/oschwald/geoip2-golang   v1.13.0  ← canonical Go MaxMind
#                                                  DB / GeoIP reader
#                                                  library (this axis)
#                                                  — by Gregory
#                                                  Oschwald (oschwald/
#                                                  geoip2-golang); pure-
#                                                  Go reader for the
#                                                  MaxMind binary
#                                                  database format
#                                                  (`.mmdb`) used by
#                                                  GeoIP2-City /
#                                                  GeoIP2-Country /
#                                                  GeoIP2-ISP /
#                                                  GeoIP2-ASN and the
#                                                  free GeoLite2
#                                                  distributions.
#                                                  Wraps the lower-
#                                                  level oschwald/
#                                                  maxminddb-golang
#                                                  (the bare wire-
#                                                  format reader)
#                                                  with the typed
#                                                  record shapes
#                                                  (geoip2.City,
#                                                  geoip2.Country,
#                                                  geoip2.ASN, etc).
#                                                  Notable: SAME
#                                                  MAINTAINER (Gregory
#                                                  Oschwald) ALSO
#                                                  authors the canonical
#                                                  Rust reader
#                                                  (`maxminddb-rust`)
#                                                  — single-author
#                                                  cross-language
#                                                  ownership, unusual
#                                                  on these axes.
#                                                  Used by virtually
#                                                  every Go networking
#                                                  / observability /
#                                                  proxy tool that
#                                                  needs IP
#                                                  geolocation:
#                                                  grafana/loki,
#                                                  crowdsecurity/
#                                                  crowdsec, owncast,
#                                                  baidu/openrasp,
#                                                  Caddy's IP filter,
#                                                  Traefik's GeoIP
#                                                  middleware, Hugo's
#                                                  IP-based rendering
#                                                  hooks.  echoip is
#                                                  the canonical
#                                                  reference consumer
#                                                  — its `iputil/geo`
#                                                  package opens up to
#                                                  three .mmdb files
#                                                  (country / city /
#                                                  ASN, all optional)
#                                                  and queries each
#                                                  database per
#                                                  incoming request to
#                                                  build the JSON/HTML/
#                                                  text response.
#   github.com/oschwald/maxminddb-golang v1.13.0  (indirect — the bare
#                                                  wire-format reader
#                                                  that geoip2-golang
#                                                  wraps)
#
# echoip runs as a tiny HTTP server that responds to GET / with the
# requester's IP and (if configured with `.mmdb` databases via `-f`/
# `-c`/`-a`) country / city / ASN information.  Content negotiation
# returns plain text by default (for curl-on-the-command-line use),
# JSON if `Accept: application/json`, or an HTML template if Accept:
# text/html.  Optional `-r` enables reverse DNS lookups, `-p` enables
# port scanning of the requester (curl-friendly "is port 22 open on
# my IP?" check via `/port/22`), `-H X-Real-IP` lets the service run
# behind a reverse proxy by trusting the forwarded IP header.  The
# public reference deployment at https://ifconfig.co is the canonical
# instance — millions of dev shell scripts curl it as
# `curl ifconfig.co` to discover their public IP.
#
# === AXIS 186 CONTINUES — MaxMind DB / GeoIP IP geolocation reader =========
# Axis position: Go=241 continues Axis 186 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# MaxMind DB reader is `github.com/oschwald/geoip2-golang` by Gregory
# Oschwald — the SAME maintainer who authors the canonical Rust reader
# (`oschwald/maxminddb-rust` covered in the previous round's _netwatch
# completion).  Same author across two lanes is rare on cross-language
# axes; the Rust and Go libraries share API conventions (Reader.Lookup
# vs Reader.City / Reader.Country / Reader.ASN methods), record-type
# shapes (City / Country / ISP / ASN / Domain / AnonymousIP), and the
# underlying binary format spec (MaxMind .mmdb) by design — Gregory
# Oschwald maintains both to a coordinated shape.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=241     _netwatch            ← previous round (axis 186 OPENS, 1/0/0)
#   Go=241       ← THIS FILE          (axis 186 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=241  ← next round         (axis 186 CLOSES at triple-241, 1/1/1)
#
# Cross-language design contrast for axis 186:
#   Rust    : maxminddb (oschwald) — single-crate reader; users
#             instantiate `maxminddb::Reader::open_readfile(path)?`
#             and then either call typed `.lookup::<geoip2::City>(ip)?`
#             with serde-deserialized records OR use the generic
#             `.lookup_prefix::<T>(...)` for custom record types.
#   Go      : geoip2-golang (oschwald) — TWO-PACKAGE design with
#             explicit separation: the bare `maxminddb-golang` reader
#             handles wire format, and `geoip2-golang` adds the typed
#             record shapes on top.  Reflects Go's preference for
#             discoverable single-purpose packages over Rust's
#             feature-gated single-crate approach.
#   JS/Node : maxmind (Egor Runov runk/node-maxmind) — different
#             maintainer from the Rust/Go lanes; pure-JS reader for
#             the same `.mmdb` format with the same record types.
#             [TBD next round]
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_echoip() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '-h[show help]' \
        '(-h --help)--help[show help]' \
        '-f[path to GeoIP country database (.mmdb)]:file:_files -g "*.(mmdb|MMDB)"' \
        '-c[path to GeoIP city database (.mmdb)]:file:_files -g "*.(mmdb|MMDB)"' \
        '-a[path to GeoIP ASN database (.mmdb)]:file:_files -g "*.(mmdb|MMDB)"' \
        '-l[listening address (default :8080)]:addr:' \
        '-r[perform reverse hostname lookups on requester IPs]' \
        '-p[enable port lookup (/port/<n> handler that scans whether the requester has port <n> open)]' \
        '-t[path to HTML template directory (default html)]:dir:_files -/' \
        '-C[size of response cache (0 disables caching; default 0)]:size:' \
        '-P[enable net/http/pprof profiling handlers at /debug/pprof/]' \
        '-s[show sponsor logo on the HTML page]' \
        '*-H[header to trust for the remote IP when behind a reverse proxy (e.g. X-Real-IP, X-Forwarded-For; repeat for multiple)]:header:(X-Real-IP X-Forwarded-For CF-Connecting-IP True-Client-IP Fastly-Client-IP X-Client-IP)'
}

_echoip "$@"
